title: Sector accounts; key figures
maintainer_displayname: ZBO | Centraal Bureau voor de Statistiek
name: sector-accounts-key-figures
notes:
This table presents a number of key figures of the sector accounts. These main indicators provide the most important information on the total economy and on the main institutional sectors of the economy: non-financial corporations, financial corporations, general government, households including non-profit institutions serving households and the rest of the world.

Data available from: 
Annual figures from 1995.
Quarterly figures current account from first quarter 1999.
Quarterly figures financial accounts and balance sheets general government.
Quarterly figures financial accounts and balance sheets all sectors from first quarter 2010.

Status of the figures:
The figures for the most recent reporting year 2013 are provisional. The figures for 2012 are revised provisional. The figures for 2011 are final.

All national accounts figures for 1995-2010 are provisional. This is because the revision of the national accounts has not been completed for the years before 2011. The revision, among other things, is needed to incorporate the European System of Accounts 2010. 

Changes as of March 26th 2015:
Data of the fourth quarter 2014 and annual data 2014 have been added to the table. Data of the first three quarters of 2014 have been revised.
 
When will new figures be published?
New data are published within 90 days after the end of each quarter. Quarterly data of the previous three quarters are adjusted along with the publication of the fourth quarter (end of March). This concurs with the first estimation of annual data of the previous year. The annual and quarterly data of the last three years are revised together with the publication of the first quarter (end of June).
